                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17340</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-03T14:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Villa left Pacheco Point, near Madeara, March 1 with 300 men headed towards
                    Columbus, New Mexico. He is reported west of Casas Grandes today. There is
                    reason, to believe he intends to cross to the United States and hopes to proceed
                    to Washington. Please consider this possibility and the necessity of
                    instructions to us on the border.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
